snippet.textDisplay: That gray colored dirt you found and are using is called 'stone dust'.  It's what the name implies, it's crushed stone and sometimes recycled concrete blended in.  It's used as a base layer under pavers, driveways, etc.  When you pack it tightly it'll harden up, which is why it's a good base layer.  You can order it by the truck full.

snippet.textDisplay:
Just a note to folks considering a mini-tiller: I led volunteers maintaining a pump track, using my Stihl mini-tiller. It worked to "carve" and shape packed soil. Then my stepdad passed, leaving me his Mantis unit. Faster time speed helps but ergonomics far superior...and adding a loop in the brush proved much easier with the Mantis; cleaning debris out of the times was faster and easier.
Given the choice, I'd buy a Mantis for this duty.
snippet.textOriginal:
